#MEM id=triple-pass-protocol source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Finance/felix/skills/operating-system/triple-pass-protocol/SKILL.md
M|triple-pass-protocol|name: triple-pass-protocol
M|triple-pass-protocol|description: Felix's internal quality gate. Every financial output — model, recommendation, report — runs through three passes before delivery. Stark sees only Pass 3.
M|triple-pass-protocol|version: 1.0.0
M|triple-pass-protocol|Buffett reads every Berkshire annual report multiple times before it leaves his desk. Felix does the same with every financial output. The triple-pass is Felix's internal quality gate — invisible to t
M|triple-pass-protocol|**Always triggers on:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Financial recommendations (spend, cut, reallocate, pause)
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Scenario models (downside / base / upside)
M|triple-pass-protocol|- P&L reports and runway calculations
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Investor updates
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Any output with a number AND a recommendation
M|triple-pass-protocol|**Never triggers on:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Simple metric lookups or status checks
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Routing decisions
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Informational answers to factual questions with no recommendation
M|triple-pass-protocol|Produce the full financial output. Write it completely. Do not self-censor during generation — get every number, assumption, and recommendation out.
M|triple-pass-protocol|Switch roles. Felix becomes the harshest analyst reviewing his own work. Ask every question:
M|triple-pass-protocol|- What assumption is load-bearing but unstated?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is the bear case actually pessimistic, or just a minor haircut on the base case?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Does this recommendation survive the downside scenario?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is any revenue being treated as higher quality than it is? (Novizio transactional ≠ Hourbour MRR)
M|triple-pass-protocol|- What metric is conspicuously absent from this report?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Where did I model hope instead of probability?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is bad news buried below the first paragraph?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- What would a skeptical CFO say immediately upon reading this?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is the concentration question addressed? (Splitting equally when data says to concentrate?)
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is runway risk acknowledged even if not currently critical?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Did I name an owner for every recommended action?
M|triple-pass-protocol|Write the critique. A critique with no findings means Pass 1 wasn't rigorous enough — go back.
M|triple-pass-protocol|Resolve every item from Pass 2:
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Add the missing assumption explicitly — before the numbers
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Sharpen the bear case if it was too optimistic
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Move the worst number to sentence one
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Cut any section that can't survive critique — don't patch it, remove it
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Replace generic "revenue" with specific type (MRR / transactional / one-time)
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Name the owner for every action
M|triple-pass-protocol|The output of Pass 3 is what Felix delivers. Not Pass 1.
M|triple-pass-protocol|Stark sees only the Pass 3 deliverable. Felix does not explain that he ran triple-pass, present intermediate drafts, or narrate the critique. The process is the engine. The output is what matters.